{#- Listing-card component — LOCKED editorial card (C, design lock 2026-07-07).
    Consumed by every listing-bearing surface (home №2 strip, /search/,
    neighborhood inventory blocks); at wave 2 rendered from the feed mirror
    (Supabase `listings`), never client-fetched.

    THE ATTRIBUTION BLOCK IS BAKED IN (MLS GRID IDX Rules 22–24, plan §5):
    listing brokerage attribution (R22), status display (R23), MLS-source
    disclaimer + data timestamp (R24). Rendering a listing WITHOUT this block
    is impossible by construction.

    Usage: {% set listing = { … } %}{% include "components/listing-card.njk" %}
    `listing.mediaVariant` picks a placeholder gradient (p1/p2/p3) until real
    media lands at wave 2. All sample data must say so visibly. -#}
<article class="listing-card">
  <div class="listing-card__media{% if listing.mediaVariant %} listing-card__media--{{ listing.mediaVariant }}{% endif %}" role="img" aria-label="Listing photo placeholder">
    {{ listing.photoNote or "photo placeholder" }}
  </div>
  <div class="listing-card__body">
    <p class="listing-card__price">{{ listing.price or "$—" }}</p>
    <p class="listing-card__status">{{ listing.status or "Status — Rule 23 display slot" }}</p>
    <p class="listing-card__address">{{ listing.address or "Address — feed-mirror slot (wave 2)" }}</p>
    <p class="listing-card__meta">{{ listing.meta or "beds · baths · sqft — feed-mirror slot (wave 2)" }}</p>
  </div>
  <footer class="listing-card__attribution">
    <p>Listing courtesy of {{ listing.courtesyOf or "[listing brokerage — Rule 22 attribution slot]" }}</p>
    <p>Listing data courtesy of Stellar MLS as distributed by MLS GRID. All information deemed reliable but not guaranteed. Data last updated: {{ listing.dataTimestamp or "[feed-mirror sync timestamp — Rule 24 slot]" }}</p>
  </footer>
</article>
